I"Ö	<p>Like the <a href="http://www.leancrew.com/all-this/2013/12/tweaking-bigfoot-footnotes/">good doctor</a>, I knew as soon as I saw <a href="http://www.bigfootjs.com">Bigfoot</a> that I would be adding it to this site. <sup id="fnref:1" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote">1</a></sup> Iâ€™ve avoided footnotes up till now because the HTML formatting for them seemed far too <em>fiddley</em>, and the Jekyll Markdown processor I was using did not support them.</p>

<p>It turns out that adding support for footnotes in Markdown was as simple as replacing redcarpet with kramdown in the Jekyll configuration. Now, instead of mucking about with HTML that looks like this:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html">    <span class="nt">&lt;sup</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">"fnref:1"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
        <span class="nt">&lt;a</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">"#fn:1"</span> <span class="na">rel=</span><span class="s">"footnote"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>1<span class="nt">&lt;/a&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;/sup&gt;</span>

<span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"footnotes"</span><span class="nt">&gt;&lt;ol&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;li</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"footnote"</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">"fn:1"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
        <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>footnote.<span class="nt">&lt;a</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">"#fnref:1"</span> <span class="na">title=</span><span class="s">"return to article"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span> â†©<span class="nt">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>I can have nicely formatted Markdown footnotes in my text, like this:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-markdown" data-lang="markdown">Footnote inline [^1]

<span class="p">[</span><span class="ss">^1</span><span class="p">]:</span> <span class="sx">The</span> footnote text</code></pre></figure>

<p>It may not amount to much, bit I think itâ€™s a nice addition to the site.</p>

